a total of $200 \div 5=40$ (trees);
on the way back, every 8 trees are marked with one,
a total of $200 \div 8=25$ (trees);
the number of trees marked repeatedly is $200 \div (5 \times 8)=5$ (trees),
$$
\begin{array}{l}
200-(40+25-5) \\
=200-60 \\
=140 \text { (trees) }
\end{array}
$$

